      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CORLESS SNEAKY (2) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when eighth at Nowra over 365m behind Money Goes (21.62) in a Grade 5. Has ability and looks hard to stop. HIP HOP ETHICS (6) scored two back then was always well back and could manage only a 13 length 7th at this track (19.40). Was a winner at her only start from this draw. Key runner on best form. SCOTT ELYSIAN (8) scored two back then drifted back and missed the frame latest finishing a 5 length 5th at Shepparton (23.02). Comes out of a solid form race last start. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. PUSHING LIMITS (7) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
